<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-02T12:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-02T12:45:00-05:00" n="810" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 <persName corresp="#p_WRACH1">Woodward</persName> Electoral Mission/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-02T12:00:00-05:45">January 2,
                                    1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1. Department’s 227, December 31, 8 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d810fn32">Not printed.</note> I am communicating the Department’s 223,
                            December 29, 6 p.m. to President <persName corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName> by special messenger today. I am prepared to
                            release Department’s statement for publication on January 5th. I shall
                            discuss details of the Department’s telegram with President <persName corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName> on his return to Managua next
                            week, and shall report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>